1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:22,021
Who are you?

4
00:00:22,088 --> 00:00:23,288
Nice to meet you.

5
00:00:23,988 --> 00:00:26,588
I'm Ko Min Ho, Seung Ri's boyfriend.

6
00:00:28,421 --> 00:00:30,688
What? You're what?

7
00:00:33,288 --> 00:00:34,488
You got me. Hold on.

8
00:00:35,221 --> 00:00:37,288
Let's let this gentleman have this one.

9
00:00:39,788 --> 00:00:40,888
I'm truly sorry.

10
00:00:41,321 --> 00:00:42,721
You must be furious.

11
00:00:42,721 --> 00:00:45,288
Go ahead and throw that water at me.

12
00:00:49,921 --> 00:00:51,288
Are you two mocking me?

13
00:00:52,588 --> 00:00:53,888
Just my luck.

14
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:55,621
You're not going to throw it?

15
00:00:56,988 --> 00:00:57,988
Then...

16
00:00:58,988 --> 00:01:00,188
I'll do it myself.

17
00:01:05,588 --> 00:01:07,688
There. Let's call it even.

18
00:01:08,088 --> 00:01:09,788
What a lunatic!

19
00:01:16,288 --> 00:01:17,788
What on earth happened?

20
00:01:18,788 --> 00:01:21,288
Let's go.
Let's get out of here first and eat.

21
00:01:22,888 --> 00:01:25,488
I was already pissed off anyway.
This actually feels nice and cool.

22
00:01:26,688 --> 00:01:27,688
Let's go.

23
00:01:35,288 --> 00:01:36,888
Delivery.

24
00:01:37,221 --> 00:01:38,388
I didn't order anything...

25
00:01:39,921 --> 00:01:41,988
Team Manager! What's going on?

26
00:01:41,988 --> 00:01:43,688
Are you Doctor Strange or something?

27
00:01:43,988 --> 00:01:45,788
You leave work
and keep coming back every day.

28
00:01:46,288 --> 00:01:48,888
Didn't I tell you?
Without loyalty, I'm nothing.

29
00:01:49,788 --> 00:01:51,788
You don't happen to need Driver Cho
and her scooter, do you?

30
00:01:52,488 --> 00:01:53,488
Busted.

31
00:01:54,188 --> 00:01:57,088
Follow me, Driver Cho. Even a ghost
looks healthy after a good meal.

32
00:01:59,688 --> 00:02:01,621
I was really getting into a groove.

33
00:02:02,121 --> 00:02:04,588
We commute and eat together every day.

34
00:02:05,088 --> 00:02:07,521
Especially today,
he could've just eaten alone.

35
00:02:09,621 --> 00:02:10,621
There.

36
00:02:10,988 --> 00:02:12,421
This is exactly my kind of food.

37
00:02:12,788 --> 00:02:14,088
Where did you get this gimbap?

38
00:02:14,221 --> 00:02:15,688
I did some serious searching.

39
00:02:15,721 --> 00:02:18,688
I found the one most similar
to the gimbap your mother made before.

40
00:02:24,321 --> 00:02:25,588
It's really good!

41
00:02:25,988 --> 00:02:28,588
Slow down. Chew your food properly.

42
00:02:29,488 --> 00:02:30,488
I'm not a kid, you know.

43
00:02:32,221 --> 00:02:33,221
See? I told you.

44
00:02:33,788 --> 00:02:35,888
You're secretly a big eater.

45
00:02:37,788 --> 00:02:39,488
- You should eat too, Team Manager.
- Okay.

46
00:02:45,088 --> 00:02:46,088
But...

47
00:02:46,588 --> 00:02:48,621
it's definitely not as good as the one
your mother made.

48
00:02:49,988 --> 00:02:50,988
Do you still have a lot of work left?

49
00:02:51,888 --> 00:02:53,821
There's no way I'll finish today.

50
00:02:53,988 --> 00:02:56,288
But I think I'll be done by tomorrow night
at the latest.

51
00:02:56,588 --> 00:02:59,288
Okay. Then once I finish this,
I'll help you.

52
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,221
You know me, right?
There's nothing I can't do.

53
00:03:01,788 --> 00:03:04,088
I'm an amazing assistant.

54
00:03:05,188 --> 00:03:06,888
Everything always comes back
to self-praise.

55
00:03:09,088 --> 00:03:12,588
Are you okay? You suddenly got saddled
with a huge workload.

56
00:03:13,888 --> 00:03:16,588
At first, I thought it was a bit unfair,

57
00:03:16,888 --> 00:03:19,788
but the more I worked on it,
the more I realized it was necessary.

58
00:03:20,388 --> 00:03:21,988
For a fair evaluation,

59
00:03:21,988 --> 00:03:24,321
there's no one
who knows Joy better than I do.

60
00:03:24,688 --> 00:03:25,888
So I want to organize it properly.

61
00:03:25,988 --> 00:03:28,188
When it comes to Joy,
you're something else.

62
00:03:28,421 --> 00:03:30,388
You were born with a positive mindset.

63
00:03:31,888 --> 00:03:32,888
Eat up.

64
00:03:35,221 --> 00:03:36,221
I'm sorry.

65
00:03:37,588 --> 00:03:40,921
Yes, my daughter made a huge mistake.

66
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:44,421
I'm truly sorry.

67
00:03:45,588 --> 00:03:48,288
Who is it?
Why do you keep saying you're sorry?

68
00:03:49,321 --> 00:03:50,688
That little brat.

69
00:03:53,821 --> 00:03:55,421
Mom.

70
00:03:56,488 --> 00:03:59,121
What did I tell you would happen
if you ran your mouth?

71
00:03:59,521 --> 00:04:00,921
What did I tell you?

72
00:04:01,521 --> 00:04:02,521
Come on!

73
00:04:03,621 --> 00:04:05,388
Still, I'm going to protect Min Ho.

74
00:04:05,921 --> 00:04:07,021
What did you say?

75
00:04:07,321 --> 00:04:10,621
We're settling this
once and for all today.

76
00:04:10,621 --> 00:04:12,388
What's wrong? Stop it already.

77
00:04:12,488 --> 00:04:15,188
Dad, thank you. You're my lifesaver.

78
00:04:15,388 --> 00:04:16,421
I'm going to the studio.

79
00:04:16,488 --> 00:04:17,488
Get back here!

80
00:04:19,788 --> 00:04:22,088
What now? Just spit it out.

81
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:24,988
I need to talk to you, Mom.

82
00:04:26,221 --> 00:04:27,288
Sure, let's talk.

83
00:04:31,588 --> 00:04:33,088
What on earth are you thinking?

84
00:04:33,588 --> 00:04:36,288
Are you going to waste your life
hung up on Gyeol,

85
00:04:37,188 --> 00:04:38,588
who never gives you anything back?

86
00:04:38,721 --> 00:04:41,088
Is that why you signed me up
for a matchmaking agency...

87
00:04:41,088 --> 00:04:42,188
without even telling me
and made me go on a blind date?

88
00:04:42,988 --> 00:04:44,088
Why did you...

89
00:04:44,121 --> 00:04:45,488
Do you think I wanted to?

90
00:04:46,121 --> 00:04:48,688
No matter how much effort you put in,
it's obviously going nowhere.

91
00:04:48,988 --> 00:04:50,588
You keep chasing Gyeol,
and Min Ho keeps chasing you.

92
00:04:51,588 --> 00:04:53,188
And what was Min Ho thinking?

93
00:04:53,721 --> 00:04:57,021
Showing up at your blind date
and pretending to be your boyfriend?

94
00:04:57,088 --> 00:05:00,488
Even if Min Ho hadn't shown up,
I would've walked out immediately.

95
00:05:01,021 --> 00:05:03,988
So don't ever do that again. Please, Mom.

96
00:05:05,888 --> 00:05:07,488
Is Gyeol the only man in the world?

97
00:05:08,221 --> 00:05:10,421
And if Min Ho isn't right for you,

98
00:05:10,421 --> 00:05:12,321
then meet someone else.

99
00:05:12,888 --> 00:05:15,388
Who knows?
Maybe you'll find your true match.

100
00:05:16,788 --> 00:05:17,788
I'm going inside.

101
00:05:18,888 --> 00:05:20,888
- Hey, Seo Seung Ri!
- That's enough.

102
00:05:24,021 --> 00:05:25,288
I can't take this anymore.

103
00:05:28,321 --> 00:05:30,021
Is Bit Na asleep?

104
00:05:30,688 --> 00:05:32,688
Yeah, she's doing much better
now that you're here.

105
00:05:33,488 --> 00:05:36,788
Just a few days ago,
she had no energy at all.

106
00:05:39,488 --> 00:05:40,488
What are you going to do now?

107
00:05:41,388 --> 00:05:44,821
I've asked the academy
to pay me several months in advance.

108
00:05:45,288 --> 00:05:47,288
I need a deposit
if I'm going to rent a studio.

109
00:05:48,188 --> 00:05:50,588
Tomorrow, I'm moving into a study room.

110
00:05:51,221 --> 00:05:52,888
No matter how understanding he is,

111
00:05:53,488 --> 00:05:56,688
I can't keep imposing on a tenant
who's paying rent.

112
00:05:58,388 --> 00:06:01,188
If I'd known this would happen,
I never would've rented out the room.

113
00:06:02,488 --> 00:06:04,121
Let's start looking for a place tomorrow.

114
00:06:05,088 --> 00:06:08,321
I'll lend you your dad's retirement money
I set aside.

115
00:06:08,321 --> 00:06:09,321
No.

116
00:06:09,921 --> 00:06:12,588
Please don't help me.

117
00:06:12,721 --> 00:06:14,121
Just take it.

118
00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:16,521
You can pay it back with interest later.

119
00:06:16,621 --> 00:06:19,688
Right now,
I need some serious reflection...

120
00:06:20,321 --> 00:06:22,488
on my essence and existence.

121
00:06:23,421 --> 00:06:26,588
I need to think
about how I've lived my life...

122
00:06:27,088 --> 00:06:28,688
and how I'm going to live it from now on.

123
00:06:28,688 --> 00:06:30,988
Please stop
with the philosophical nonsense...

124
00:06:31,321 --> 00:06:32,988
and face reality.

125
00:06:33,421 --> 00:06:34,988
Think about Bit Na!

126
00:06:35,488 --> 00:06:37,388
Yes, Mom. I've thought about it plenty.

127
00:06:38,221 --> 00:06:39,988
And last night, Eun Ae...

128
00:06:40,688 --> 00:06:43,888
offered me the acquisition money.
I turned it down.

129
00:06:44,888 --> 00:06:46,688
What? Eun Ae did?

130
00:06:47,888 --> 00:06:50,621
You're giving me the 250,000-dollar payout
from the acquisition?

131
00:06:50,888 --> 00:06:52,588
I'm not giving it to you.

132
00:06:52,588 --> 00:06:54,921
Just pay me back
when I start my own business.

133
00:06:55,521 --> 00:06:57,588
Take that money, get a place,

134
00:06:57,921 --> 00:07:00,288
and somehow reconcile with your wife,
okay?

135
00:07:02,288 --> 00:07:06,088
It's too late.
We've already crossed the Rubicon.

136
00:07:06,121 --> 00:07:10,088
And I can't take your money.
No, I won't take it.

137
00:07:10,688 --> 00:07:11,988
Then what are you going to do?

138
00:07:12,388 --> 00:07:15,121
Are you seriously saying you're going
to live in a study room with Bit Na?

139
00:07:15,521 --> 00:07:18,021
No matter what happens,
I'm going to earn...

140
00:07:18,321 --> 00:07:20,188
a home for Bit Na and me
with my own two hands.

141
00:07:21,188 --> 00:07:24,288
Ji Seon may seem cold and selfish,

142
00:07:24,888 --> 00:07:27,488
but living with a husband like you,
who only follows his own convictions,

143
00:07:27,621 --> 00:07:29,388
must have been hard in reality.

144
00:07:29,588 --> 00:07:31,988
That's probably why she fell
for a scam like that.

145
00:07:33,288 --> 00:07:35,988
I know. What I believed was my best...

146
00:07:36,488 --> 00:07:38,288
turned out to be the worst for Ji Seon.

147
00:07:38,521 --> 00:07:40,288
Then change.

148
00:07:40,721 --> 00:07:42,921
It's not too late. You can still change.

149
00:07:43,288 --> 00:07:44,588
For Bit Na's sake, if nothing else.

150
00:07:48,421 --> 00:07:52,888
Think carefully about what I said,
and let's talk again, okay?

151
00:07:53,688 --> 00:07:56,321
See? Even Eun Ae agrees with us.

152
00:07:57,388 --> 00:08:01,188
You refuse to take your sister's money,
so listen to your mom.

153
00:08:01,788 --> 00:08:05,021
No. I can't accept help from you either.

154
00:08:06,088 --> 00:08:09,221
No matter what happens,
I'm going to start over on my own.

155
00:08:09,588 --> 00:08:11,488
That's because you're only thinking
about yourself.

156
00:08:11,488 --> 00:08:15,421
If you really cared about Bit Na,
you'd find a way back together.

157
00:08:16,288 --> 00:08:19,621
Do you want Bit Na to grow up
thinking her mom abandoned her?

158
00:08:20,388 --> 00:08:22,788
Do you have any idea
what kind of scar that will leave?

159
00:08:25,188 --> 00:08:28,088
Ji Seon didn't abandon Bit Na, Mom.

160
00:08:29,488 --> 00:08:32,288
She's trying to clean up the mess
so Bit Na and I won't get hurt.

161
00:08:33,088 --> 00:08:35,621
I'll explain everything to Bit Na.

162
00:08:36,488 --> 00:08:37,588
This is so upsetting.

163
00:08:39,688 --> 00:08:40,988
Go upstairs and get some rest.

164
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:43,088
Honey, let's go inside.

165
00:08:46,021 --> 00:08:47,388
Here are the printouts.

166
00:08:47,521 --> 00:08:50,021
For the final review,
these will be better than a monitor.

167
00:08:50,688 --> 00:08:51,788
Thank you.

168
00:08:55,721 --> 00:08:56,788
Want to take a short break?

169
00:08:57,388 --> 00:09:00,088
No. The sooner I finish this,
the sooner I can get back to the team.

170
00:09:02,621 --> 00:09:05,521
Get up for a minute.
Let's at least get some fresh air.

171
00:09:06,721 --> 00:09:09,521
Managing your well-being
is part of my duties as your assistant.

172
00:09:12,188 --> 00:09:13,188
Managing my well-being?

173
00:09:14,188 --> 00:09:17,321
Why is an assistant
talking in such a deep voice?

174
00:09:17,988 --> 00:09:19,388
So full of charisma.

175
00:09:23,088 --> 00:09:24,788
The night air feels great.

176
00:09:25,988 --> 00:09:28,088
I told you it'd be nice to come outside.

177
00:09:28,521 --> 00:09:31,788
Yes. The weather is nice again today.

178
00:10:02,088 --> 00:10:04,421
You asked me before, right?

179
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:08,988
About what happens when I leave.

180
00:10:11,421 --> 00:10:13,255
Well, I meant...

181
00:10:13,255 --> 00:10:17,421
what happens to Our Happy Home.

182
00:10:20,388 --> 00:10:21,821
I've been thinking about it too.

183
00:10:23,388 --> 00:10:24,788
"What will happen to us?"

184
00:10:25,988 --> 00:10:29,188
"Will the home we've built
ever be completed?"

185
00:10:32,221 --> 00:10:33,688
We've already started.

186
00:10:35,188 --> 00:10:39,188
Although no one knows where it will end.

187
00:10:44,721 --> 00:10:46,388
Can you walk a road...

188
00:10:47,521 --> 00:10:50,121
when you don't know where it leads,
Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

189
00:10:54,088 --> 00:10:55,688
Can you really stop your heart...

190
00:10:56,788 --> 00:11:00,721
because of something
that hasn't happened yet?

191
00:11:05,721 --> 00:11:07,421
I think you're very brave.

192
00:11:08,288 --> 00:11:10,621
Or maybe reckless.

193
00:11:12,388 --> 00:11:16,388
You might end up getting hurt.

194
00:11:17,621 --> 00:11:18,888
I told you.

195
00:11:19,988 --> 00:11:23,088
I live for today.

196
00:11:57,721 --> 00:12:01,121
Are you really leaving?

197
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:05,788
Then what about me?

198
00:12:14,988 --> 00:12:15,988
Beautiful.

199
00:12:20,888 --> 00:12:21,921
I mean, the night view.

200
00:12:23,821 --> 00:12:27,121
I never knew Seoul's night view
could rival New York's.

201
00:12:28,621 --> 00:12:32,021
The night view. Yes, it's beautiful.

202
00:12:36,188 --> 00:12:38,021
Should we head back down?

203
00:12:43,788 --> 00:12:46,488
Do you...

204
00:12:50,888 --> 00:12:51,888
really have to go?

205
00:13:20,888 --> 00:13:21,888
How dare you come in here?

206
00:13:23,088 --> 00:13:25,521
Have you lost your mind?
Get out right now.

207
00:13:33,088 --> 00:13:34,988
Hey, didn't you hear me
tell you to get out?

208
00:13:38,988 --> 00:13:42,621
Ms. Cho, it's my time right now.

209
00:13:44,588 --> 00:13:46,021
Where did the time go?

210
00:13:46,721 --> 00:13:49,588
It's bad enough you're using my time slot.

211
00:13:50,088 --> 00:13:52,088
And now, you're telling me to get out?

212
00:13:52,088 --> 00:13:54,721
Not you. Intern Yu Jin Seok.

213
00:13:55,288 --> 00:13:57,988
An intern barging into the operating room
like he owns the place.

214
00:13:58,088 --> 00:13:59,588
That's who I'm talking to.

215
00:14:00,488 --> 00:14:02,021
I see.

216
00:14:02,021 --> 00:14:05,288
Yu Jin Seok,
you've got some nerve for an intern.

217
00:14:05,288 --> 00:14:06,388
Exactly.

218
00:14:06,388 --> 00:14:07,421
Wait a second, Ms. Cho.

219
00:14:09,888 --> 00:14:11,221
Did you happen to forget that?

220
00:14:13,788 --> 00:14:14,788
Seriously.

221
00:14:18,288 --> 00:14:19,288
There, okay?

222
00:14:19,688 --> 00:14:21,888
Please give me back my change.

223
00:14:40,888 --> 00:14:43,621
Oh Hye Ji,
what brings you here without even calling?

224
00:14:44,688 --> 00:14:47,421
Eun Nim, why are you here at this hour?

225
00:14:50,321 --> 00:14:51,888
Hello, Mr. Seo.

226
00:14:52,821 --> 00:14:53,821
Hello.

227
00:15:03,788 --> 00:15:06,021
Mr. Seo, have some late-night snacks.

228
00:15:07,188 --> 00:15:08,188
Late-night snacks!

229
00:15:08,588 --> 00:15:10,421
There's even beer. Hold on.

230
00:15:13,888 --> 00:15:15,721
Aren't you going home?
The buses will stop running soon.

231
00:15:22,521 --> 00:15:25,321
Come on. Let's all have a drink together.

232
00:15:26,021 --> 00:15:27,488
Yes, Mr. Seo.

233
00:15:28,188 --> 00:15:29,188
Cheers.

234
00:15:38,388 --> 00:15:39,388
You know, Hye Ji,

235
00:15:39,721 --> 00:15:42,788
when you walked through that door,

236
00:15:42,988 --> 00:15:46,688
you were shining so brightly
I almost had to put on sunglasses.

237
00:15:46,988 --> 00:15:48,888
There was this glowing aura around you.

238
00:15:50,721 --> 00:15:53,688
The moment I walked into the studio,

239
00:15:53,688 --> 00:15:57,421
I thought someone
had turned on 500 fluorescent lights.

240
00:15:57,888 --> 00:16:00,388
You people are really something else.

241
00:16:08,321 --> 00:16:10,988
Why are you suddenly saying
you're not going?

242
00:16:11,488 --> 00:16:15,488
That restaurant serves
authentic French home cooking.

243
00:16:16,288 --> 00:16:17,288
I'm sorry.

244
00:16:17,988 --> 00:16:20,221
I've been feeling under the weather
since last night.

245
00:16:21,121 --> 00:16:22,621
Why all of a sudden?

246
00:16:23,088 --> 00:16:25,421
You're not planning to leave me out...

247
00:16:25,421 --> 00:16:27,288
and go hang out alone
with Kang Yeon Ja, are you?

248
00:16:27,488 --> 00:16:28,488
What?

249
00:16:29,588 --> 00:16:32,688
I'm hanging up now.
I already feel awful enough.

250
00:16:32,688 --> 00:16:33,721
Wait.

251
00:16:34,288 --> 00:16:36,688
Then could you send me the address...

252
00:16:36,688 --> 00:16:38,288
of Kang Yeon Ja's real estate office?

253
00:16:38,588 --> 00:16:40,688
What? Why?

254
00:16:41,121 --> 00:16:42,821
No reason.

255
00:16:43,021 --> 00:16:45,688
I already got ready to go out,

256
00:16:45,888 --> 00:16:47,988
and it feels like a waste
to just stay home.

257
00:16:49,121 --> 00:16:50,121
You didn't know?

258
00:16:50,788 --> 00:16:53,521
I invest in land.

259
00:16:54,121 --> 00:16:55,888
Buying land when I'm bored is my hobby.

260
00:16:56,688 --> 00:16:57,688
What?

261
00:16:57,688 --> 00:16:58,988
I just want to see...

262
00:16:59,088 --> 00:17:01,821
what kind of amazing real estate business
she's running...

263
00:17:02,288 --> 00:17:03,588
that makes her act so high and mighty.

264
00:17:05,888 --> 00:17:06,888
All right.

265
00:17:07,221 --> 00:17:10,821
I'll take a picture of the business card
and send you the address.

266
00:17:11,688 --> 00:17:12,688
Now hang up already.

267
00:17:18,388 --> 00:17:19,388
Jeongdam-dong?

268
00:17:20,088 --> 00:17:22,588
Where on earth is Jeongdam-dong?

269
00:17:23,621 --> 00:17:26,588
Maybe I'll go there
and buy the biggest building in town...

270
00:17:26,988 --> 00:17:29,788
just to crush her pride. Seriously.

271
00:17:33,021 --> 00:17:35,388
Why would she go there
just to embarrass herself again?

272
00:17:38,488 --> 00:17:41,288
Why hasn't Seung Wu come home yet?

273
00:17:41,988 --> 00:17:44,388
Didn't he say he had to leave the studio
by 9 a.m.?

274
00:17:45,888 --> 00:17:47,221
It's already past 11.

275
00:18:07,088 --> 00:18:08,988
Wait, what happened?

276
00:18:10,221 --> 00:18:11,388
Where did Hye Ji go?

277
00:18:12,921 --> 00:18:15,421
What on earth happened last night?

278
00:18:20,521 --> 00:18:21,588
She probably can't see me.

279
00:18:22,021 --> 00:18:25,288
Should I just quietly make a run for it?

280
00:18:33,388 --> 00:18:34,421
You brat, stop right there!

281
00:18:35,988 --> 00:18:38,388
Do you think the ER is a place for punks
like you to fool around and date?

282
00:18:38,688 --> 00:18:40,588
If that's how you're going to act,
then quit.

283
00:18:40,988 --> 00:18:43,021
Get out right now. Get lost!

284
00:18:52,588 --> 00:18:53,588
Where did he go?

285
00:18:56,121 --> 00:18:58,721
Darn it.
He ran off without even cleaning up.

286
00:19:02,988 --> 00:19:04,088
Are you brewing some medicine, Mother?

287
00:19:05,488 --> 00:19:09,488
At first, the smell of herbal medicine
really bothered me, but now I like it.

288
00:19:09,688 --> 00:19:10,821
I guess I've gotten used to it.

289
00:19:11,688 --> 00:19:13,388
That's good to hear.

290
00:19:13,688 --> 00:19:14,888
Has it been helping at all?

291
00:19:15,188 --> 00:19:19,088
Father seems to cough less than before
and looks much better.

292
00:19:19,488 --> 00:19:20,988
He doesn't seem to be in much pain either.

293
00:19:21,621 --> 00:19:25,288
Well, that's because he's taking
painkillers for the pain.

294
00:19:26,721 --> 00:19:29,288
I don't really know
whether it's working or not,

295
00:19:29,988 --> 00:19:32,088
but I'll try anything
that's supposed to help.

296
00:19:33,121 --> 00:19:36,188
It seems your devotion
is finally paying off, Mother.

297
00:19:43,388 --> 00:19:45,721
I guess
I shouldn't have spoken carelessly.

298
00:19:51,488 --> 00:19:52,688
(Message)

299
00:19:59,688 --> 00:20:02,588
We met at the police station last time.

300
00:20:03,788 --> 00:20:05,421
I've been thinking about it,

301
00:20:06,488 --> 00:20:09,121
and the timing overlaps
with the adoption annulment in France.

302
00:20:10,088 --> 00:20:12,688
I can't shake the feeling
that you might be my mother.

303
00:20:13,388 --> 00:20:16,688
Then does that mean Mother's daughter
was adopted overseas?

304
00:20:18,088 --> 00:20:19,688
This is shocking!

305
00:20:19,821 --> 00:20:21,488
(Delete)

306
00:20:25,288 --> 00:20:27,921
If the DNA test proves
she's really her daughter...

307
00:20:29,788 --> 00:20:30,821
That can't happen.

308
00:20:33,421 --> 00:20:37,088
Even with the pain patches,
it still hurts a lot, doesn't it?

309
00:20:38,088 --> 00:20:39,088
No.

310
00:20:40,888 --> 00:20:42,888
I'm sorry for scaring you, Yeong Hwa.

311
00:20:43,488 --> 00:20:45,121
Why would you apologize to me?

312
00:20:46,588 --> 00:20:49,188
Don't worry about me.
If you're in pain, say you're in pain.

313
00:20:50,021 --> 00:20:52,788
If you're struggling,
say you're struggling. Don't endure it.

314
00:20:53,088 --> 00:20:54,821
I'm really okay.

315
00:20:57,288 --> 00:21:01,088
The biggest thing I need to do
before I leave...

316
00:21:02,588 --> 00:21:05,388
is help you find Yeon Sun.

317
00:21:06,888 --> 00:21:08,821
Until I finish that task,

318
00:21:09,988 --> 00:21:13,988
I'll stay healthy and strong,
so don't worry.

319
00:21:17,988 --> 00:21:19,821
Let's go inside.

320
00:21:22,621 --> 00:21:23,688
Bit Na, are you sleepy?

321
00:21:23,888 --> 00:21:26,121
Yes. We played the train game...

322
00:21:26,121 --> 00:21:28,588
at kindergarten today, so I'm tired.

323
00:21:29,488 --> 00:21:30,988
Then just sleep for 30 minutes.

324
00:21:31,488 --> 00:21:33,821
If you nap too long,
you won't be able to sleep tonight.

325
00:21:33,988 --> 00:21:36,088
Sleep here. Lie down.

326
00:21:45,088 --> 00:21:46,088
Hello?

327
00:21:47,921 --> 00:21:49,288
Long-term rentals
are hard to find these days,

328
00:21:49,288 --> 00:21:52,288
but I do have a couple of hybrid leases.
Would you like to see them?

329
00:21:54,088 --> 00:21:55,888
Then come to the real estate office now.

330
00:21:57,121 --> 00:21:58,121
Okay.

331
00:21:59,488 --> 00:22:01,888
Grandma has to go show houses to a client.

332
00:22:01,888 --> 00:22:04,988
You sleep, okay?

333
00:22:05,621 --> 00:22:07,921
When you wake up, call me.

334
00:22:08,821 --> 00:22:10,588
Have a safe trip.

335
00:22:11,021 --> 00:22:12,221
My granddaughter.

336
00:22:15,821 --> 00:22:17,088
(Kangsu Construction)

337
00:22:17,088 --> 00:22:18,488
What? Overseas adoption?

338
00:22:20,188 --> 00:22:21,221
Are you sure?

339
00:22:23,121 --> 00:22:25,621
Yeah, deleting that text
was definitely the right move.

340
00:22:26,288 --> 00:22:27,288
Okay, bye.

341
00:22:29,121 --> 00:22:30,121
An overseas adoption...

342
00:22:31,088 --> 00:22:33,021
Is that why they couldn't find her
for so long?

343
00:22:34,888 --> 00:22:37,588
Why do I keep feeling so uneasy?

344
00:22:46,488 --> 00:22:48,788
What brings you to the secretary's office?

345
00:22:49,321 --> 00:22:51,088
Nothing. I'm just...

346
00:22:51,488 --> 00:22:53,988
making the rounds
and checking in on the employees.

347
00:22:54,588 --> 00:22:57,388
By the way, where's Mr. Seo?

348
00:22:58,021 --> 00:23:01,488
He was here just a little while ago.
Did you need to tell him something?

349
00:23:02,721 --> 00:23:03,721
No.

350
00:23:08,388 --> 00:23:12,488
You two share the secretary's office.
Any inconveniences?

351
00:23:12,988 --> 00:23:13,988
None.

352
00:23:15,321 --> 00:23:16,321
That's good.

353
00:23:17,388 --> 00:23:18,988
He keeps his desk nice and tidy.

354
00:23:24,921 --> 00:23:26,988
Hey, Mr. Cho.

355
00:23:27,688 --> 00:23:29,421
Could you get me...

356
00:23:29,888 --> 00:23:32,121
a sweet, cold drink from the café
in the lobby?

357
00:23:32,121 --> 00:23:34,621
I feel like I need a sugar boost.

358
00:23:35,188 --> 00:23:38,088
Sure. What would you like?

359
00:23:40,221 --> 00:23:41,221
Well...

360
00:23:41,888 --> 00:23:44,221
An iced salted caramel hazelnut latte...

361
00:23:44,221 --> 00:23:47,121
with mascarpone cream and an extra shot.

362
00:23:48,221 --> 00:23:50,621
And only half the hazelnut syrup.

363
00:23:50,888 --> 00:23:52,388
Extra mascarpone cream.

364
00:23:52,588 --> 00:23:53,588
And,

365
00:23:54,688 --> 00:23:57,388
you know the cinnamon powder?
Just a little of that.

366
00:23:57,888 --> 00:24:00,821
Excuse me? Could you say that again?

367
00:24:00,821 --> 00:24:03,121
An iced salted caramel hazel...

368
00:24:03,821 --> 00:24:04,821
What was that?

369
00:24:05,088 --> 00:24:06,888
Yeah, it's hard to remember.

370
00:24:07,088 --> 00:24:09,288
Just tell them it's my favorite menu item.

371
00:24:09,288 --> 00:24:10,988
They'll know what it is.

372
00:24:11,688 --> 00:24:13,921
And while you're there,
get something for yourself too.

373
00:24:14,788 --> 00:24:15,788
There's a drink on the menu called...

374
00:24:16,288 --> 00:24:19,488
a choux cream pistachio blended latte.

375
00:24:19,488 --> 00:24:21,721
No, thank you. I'm fine.

376
00:24:22,721 --> 00:24:25,388
Please wait in your office.
I'll bring it to you.

377
00:24:25,588 --> 00:24:26,721
All right, then. Thanks for your help.

378
00:24:26,888 --> 00:24:29,188
I'll be in my office. The CEO's office.

379
00:24:29,221 --> 00:24:30,621
- Let's go. Go on.
- Yes, sir.

380
00:24:30,988 --> 00:24:31,988
Sorry.

381
00:24:45,388 --> 00:24:48,788
What's this? Yoon Image Forensics Lab?

382
00:24:59,221 --> 00:25:00,221
What is this?

383
00:25:02,488 --> 00:25:03,588
What do you think you're doing?

384
00:25:08,888 --> 00:25:12,121
Yeah, it's embarrassing for someone
in my position as CEO...

385
00:25:12,121 --> 00:25:13,788
to be caught doing something like this,

386
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:18,088
but why are you hiding things from me
to that extent?

387
00:25:18,388 --> 00:25:20,588
Do you think I'd do something
if Mother found her daughter?

388
00:25:21,088 --> 00:25:22,221
It's the Chairman's order.

389
00:25:23,288 --> 00:25:24,788
He said not to disclose any information
to anyone.

390
00:25:26,188 --> 00:25:28,521
You must think I'm some kind of idiot.

391
00:25:28,988 --> 00:25:32,488
Hey, I heard she was adopted overseas.
France or somewhere.

392
00:25:35,988 --> 00:25:39,088
Gwon Sik,
there are no secrets in this world.

393
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:41,188
No matter how much you try
to hide something,

394
00:25:41,188 --> 00:25:42,821
the truth always comes out eventually.

395
00:25:44,588 --> 00:25:48,188
Haven't you heard the saying
about an awl in a sack?

396
00:25:49,188 --> 00:25:50,488
Then we'll find out when the time comes.

397
00:25:51,188 --> 00:25:52,888
When the awl pokes through the sack.

398
00:26:18,588 --> 00:26:19,888
(Cho Eun Nim)

399
00:26:21,421 --> 00:26:24,621
How cute. It looks like doll clothes.

400
00:26:30,721 --> 00:26:31,788
What's this?

401
00:26:37,921 --> 00:26:40,221
Excuse me. Is anyone here?

402
00:26:44,088 --> 00:26:47,388
Seriously.
She runs a tiny little shop like this...

403
00:26:47,388 --> 00:26:48,788
and still acts all high and mighty?

404
00:26:49,788 --> 00:26:52,821
You get a few certificates,
and now you're all that?

405
00:26:55,788 --> 00:26:58,188
What's that? Is that the main house?

406
00:27:06,621 --> 00:27:07,621
Hey, kid.

407
00:27:08,621 --> 00:27:12,221
Hey, is this the home
of the real estate office owner?

408
00:27:12,521 --> 00:27:15,088
Yes, it's my grandma's house.

409
00:27:15,088 --> 00:27:17,588
Really? Where did your grandma go?

410
00:27:17,788 --> 00:27:19,988
She went to show houses to a client.

411
00:27:20,988 --> 00:27:22,388
But who are you?

412
00:27:22,721 --> 00:27:25,621
Me? Your grandma's friend.

413
00:27:29,721 --> 00:27:30,721
What's this?

414
00:27:33,788 --> 00:27:36,021
It's not even an expensive piece.

415
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:39,888
Why would she keep a cheap necklace
like this hidden away?

416
00:27:40,488 --> 00:27:43,388
Hey, what's that necklace?

417
00:27:44,721 --> 00:27:46,488
It belongs to my grandma.

418
00:27:47,188 --> 00:27:50,921
What?
Could I take a look at it for a second?

419
00:27:51,621 --> 00:27:52,621
Sure.

420
00:28:02,588 --> 00:28:03,588
My goodness.

421
00:28:05,821 --> 00:28:06,821
Bit Na!

422
00:28:22,021 --> 00:28:24,721
(Our Happy Days)

423
00:28:24,888 --> 00:28:27,788
Cho Eun Ae, he said no.

424
00:28:27,921 --> 00:28:29,488
Please stop thinking about it. Just stop.

425
00:28:29,788 --> 00:28:31,688
Do you want today to be our first day?

426
00:28:31,688 --> 00:28:33,388
- Let's date.
- What?

427
00:28:34,188 --> 00:28:35,421
Okay, deal.

428
00:28:35,688 --> 00:28:37,421
Seriously, you're full of love.

429
00:28:37,588 --> 00:28:38,588
Team Manager.

430
00:28:38,688 --> 00:28:40,788
I like you, Team Manager.

431
00:28:40,812 --> 00:28:52,512
resynced by luvmichelle
